        "text": "λ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "whom He has not raised, if really thus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (as is asserted) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "dead persons are not raised",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Regarding ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰ ἄρα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἴπερ ἄρα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", see Klotz, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "l.c.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " pp. 178, 528. Observe here (1) the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "identity of the category",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in which Paul places the resurrection of Christ and the bodily resurrection of the dead; (2) the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sacredness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the apostolic testimony for the former; (3) the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "fanatical self-deception",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", to which he would have been a victim, if the appearances of the Risen One had been psychological hallucinations, so that the whole transformation of Saul into Paul—nay, his whole Gospel—would rest upon this self-deception, and this self-deception upon a mental weakness which would be totally irreconcilable with his otherwise well-known strength and acuteness of intellect.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
