    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ψευδομάρτυρες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "false witnesses",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") It is not lawful to declare concerning God what is not so; although it may seem to give glory to Him. False witnesses are, for instance, traders, who, for the sake of their gain, give fictitious accounts of earthquakes, inundations, and other great calamities, which have happened in distant countries, and lead souls otherwise not too credulous to thoughts and conversations concerning ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "divine",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " judgments, good in the proposition (thesis), but erroneous in the supposition (hypothesis) on which the proposition rests.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
